{"lemma":"بَذَّ","slug":"بَذَّ","root":"ب.ذ.ذ","root_slug":"ب-ذ-ذ","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ذ-ذ","pos":"V","pos_camel":"verb","paradigm":[{"role":"past_2ms","form":"بَذَذْتَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"past_2fs","form":"بَذَذْتِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"past_2md","form":"بَذَذْتُما","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"past_2mp","form":"بَذَذْتُم","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_2fp","form":"بَذَذْتُنَّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"past_3ms","form":"بَذَّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"past_3fs","form":"بَذَّت","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"past_3md","form":"بَذّا","in_corpus":true,"count":3,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"past_3fd","form":"بَذَّتا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"past_3mp","form":"بَذُّوا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_3fp","form":"بَذَذْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2ms","form":"تَبُذّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2ms","form":"تَبْذُذ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2fs","form":"تَبُذِّي","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2fs","form":"تَبُذِّينَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2md","form":"تَبُذّا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_2md","form":"تَبُذّانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_2mp","form":"تَبُذُّوا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2mp","form":"تَبُذُّونَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2fp","form":"تَبْذُذْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3ms","form":"يَبُذّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3ms","form":"يَبْذُذ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3fs","form":"تَبُذّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3fs","form":"تَبْذُذ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3md","form":"يَبُذّا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3md","form":"يَبُذّانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3fd","form":"تَبُذّا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3fd","form":"تَبُذّانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3mp","form":"يَبُذُّوا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3mp","form":"يَبُذُّونَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3fp","form":"يَبْذُذْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_1mp","form":"نَبُذّ","in_corpus":true,"count":2,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_1ms","form":"أَبُذّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"past_1mp","form":"بَذَذْنا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1ms","form":"بَذَذْتُ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"}],"frequency_in_corpus":5,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2064"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B0%D9%8E%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to beat, surpass"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/bað.ða/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2064","headword_ar":"بَذَّ","root":"b*","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) sec. pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba*i*ota","text_ar":"بَذِذْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaba*~u","text_ar":"يَبَذُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba*aA*apN","text_ar":"بَذَاذَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Mgh, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bu*uw*apN","text_ar":"بُذُوذَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba*a*N","text_ar":"بَذَذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Mgh, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba*aA*N","text_ar":"بَذَاذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi*aA*N","text_ar":"بِذَاذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr, (TA,) [of all which, the third is the regular form,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, threadbare, and shabby,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mean, in the state of his apparel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, S, M, Mgh, L,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in an evil condition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slovenly with respect to his person:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, M, L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he neglected the constant adornment of himself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he adorned himself one day, and another day left his hair in a shaggy"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dishevelled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"matted and dusty, state:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was humble in his apparel, not taking pleasure therein."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, L.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba*aA*ap","text_ar":"بَذَاذَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said in a trad. to be a part of religion; (Ks, T, M, Mgh, L;) meaning, in this instance, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being humble in dress, and wearing that which is not conducive to self-conceit and pride."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba*~ahu","text_ar":"بَذَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabu*~u","text_ar":"يَبُذُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, L,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba*~N","text_ar":"بَذٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, L, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba*iy*apN","text_ar":"بَذِيذَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) [or this may be a simple subst.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He overcame him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, L, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he surpassed him"},{"kind":"text","text":"in goodliness or beauty, or in any deed: (T, L:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he outstripped him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba*~a AlqaAy^iliyna","text_ar":"بَذَّ القَايِلِينَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He outstripped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surpassed, and overcame, the speakers."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)"}],"source_refs":["M","S","Mgh","K","L","TA","Ks","T"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%A8%D8%B0/","headword_ar":"بذ","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_36","lexicon_en":"Al-Ṣāḥib bin ʿAbbād, Al-Muḥīṭ fī l-Lugha (d. c. 995 CE)","lexicon_ar":"المحيط في اللغة للصاحب بن عباد","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=10817#3322b9","body_html":"<span>بذ: بَذَّه يَبُذُّه: إذا سَبَقَه في الحُسْنِ فيما كانَ.</span><br><span>وباذّذْتُه الشَّيْءَ: أي بادَرْتُه.</span><br><span>وابْتَذَذْتُ حَقّي منه: أخَذْتُه.</span><br><span>وأخَذْتُ منه بَذِيْذَتِي وبَذّي: أي نَصِيْبي وحَقّي.</span><br><span>وفلانٌ بَذِيْذِي: أي مِثْلي، وبِذّي وبَذّي: مِثْلُه.</span><br><span>والبَذَاذَةُ: سُوْءُ الهَيْئَةِ، في هَيْئَتِه بَذَاذَةٌ وبَذَّةٌ، ورَجُلٌ بَذِيْذٌ وباذٌّ وبَذٌّ، وبَذِذْتَ يا فلانٌ.</span><br><span>ورَجُلٌ فَذٌّ بَذٌّ: أي فَرْدٌ، وأحَذُّ أبَذُّ. وخَصْلَةٌ حَذّاءُ بَذّاءُ: فَرْدَةٌ.</span><br><span>واسْتَبَذَّ برَأْيِه: أي اسْتَبَدَّ به.</span><br><span>والنَّاسُ هَذَاذَيْكَ وبَذَاذَيْكَ: أي هاهُنا وهاهُنا.</span><br><span>وتَمْرٌ بَذٌّ وبَثٌّ: مُتَفَرِّقٌ.</span><br><span>وبَذَّه ببَصَرِه: يُقال في شِدَّةِ النَّظَرِ.</span>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_3","lexicon_en":"Al-Khalīl b. Aḥmad al-Farāhīdī, Kitāb al-ʿAin (d. 786 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب العين للخليل بن أحمد الفراهيدي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=10817#5e0408","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">باب الذّال والباء ب ذ، ذ ب يستعملان</span><br><br><span>بذ: تقول العربُ بَذَّ يَبُذُّ بَذّاً إذا خَرَجَ شيءٌ على الآخر في حُسْن أو عَمَل كائنا ما كانَ. </span><span>والبَذاذةُ: سُوءُ الهَيْئة، ورجلٌ باذُّ الهَيئة، ولقد بَذِد وأَبَذَّهُ غَيْرُهُ.</span><br><br><span>ذب: ذبَّ يَذِبُّ ذُبُوباً وهو يُبْسُ الشَّفَةِ، وقد ذَبَّتْ شَفَتاه. وهما ذابَّتان، والجميع الذَّوابّ. وهو يَذُبُّ في الحَرْبِ عن حَريمه وأصحابه، أي يدفَع عنهم ذَبّاً. والمِذَبَّةُ التي تَذُبُّ بها الذُّبابُ، والذُّبابُ اسمٌ واحدٌ للذكَّر والأنثى، والغالب في الكلام التذكير كما أنّ الغالب في العُقاب التأنيث فلا يقولون أبداً إلاّ: هذه عُقابٌ، وانقَضَّتْ عُقاب. ويجمع الذُّبابُ على أذِبَّةٍ، فإِنْ كَثُرَ فهو الذِّبّان. وذُباب السَّيف: رأسُه الذي فيه ظُبَتُه.</span><br><br><span>وجاء في الحديث: كثمرة السوط يتبعها ذُباب السيف،</span><br><br><span>وثَمَرة السَّوْطِ: طَرَفه. والذَّبْذَبةُ: تردُّدُ شيءٍ في الهواء معلَّقٍ. والذَّباذِبُ: أشياءُ تُعَلَّق من الهَوادج، أوّل رأسِ البعير للزِّينةِ، الواحدُ ذُبْذُب، ورجلٌ مُذَبْذَبٌ ومُتَذَبْذِب أي مُتَرَدِّدٌ بين أمرَيْن وبين رَجُلَيْن لا يثبُتُ على صَحابته لأحَدٍ. والذُّباذِبُ: ذَكَرُ الرجل لأنَّه يَتَذَبْذَبُ أي يترَدَّدُ. </span><a></a>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_49","lexicon_en":"Arabic-English Lexicon by Edward William Lane (d. 1876)","lexicon_ar":"المعجم العربي الإنجليزي لإدوارد وليام لين","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=10817#608875","body_html":"<h3>بذ</h3><span class=\"sense\">1</span> بَذَّ, (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>,) sec. <abbr title=\"Persian (Farsi)\">Pers\\.</abbr> بَذِذْتَ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Mughrib of al-Mutarrizī\">Mgh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"aorist (shows the vowel of the second consonant of the aorist/muḍāriʿ form)\">aor.</abbr> ـَ (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> بَذَاذَةٌ (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Mughrib of al-Mutarrizī\">Mgh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) and بُذُوذَةٌ (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) and بَذَذٌ (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Mughrib of al-Mutarrizī\">Mgh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) and بَذَاذٌ, (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) or بِذَاذٌ, with kesr, (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) [of all which, the third is the regular form,] He (a man) was, or became, threadbare, and shabby, or mean, in the state of his apparel, (<abbr title=\"al-Kisāʾī\">Ks</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Mughrib of al-Mutarrizī\">Mgh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>,) and in an evil condition; (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>;) slovenly with respect to his person: (<abbr title=\"al-Kisāʾī\">Ks</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>:) or he neglected the constant adornment of himself: or he adorned himself one day, and another day left his hair in a shaggy or dishevelled, or matted and dusty, state: (<abbr title=\"The Tahdhīb of al-Azharī\">T</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>:) or he was humble in his apparel, not taking pleasure therein. (<abbr title=\"Ibn al-Athīr al-Jazari\">IAth</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) بَذَاذَة is said in a <abbr title=\"tradition (hadith), حَدِيْثٌ\">trad.</abbr> to be a part of religion; (<abbr title=\"al-Kisāʾī\">Ks</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tahdhīb of al-Azharī\">T</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Mughrib of al-Mutarrizī\">Mgh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>;) meaning, in this instance, The being humble in dress, and wearing that which is not conducive to self-conceit and pride. (<abbr title=\"The Mughrib of al-Mutarrizī\">Mgh</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">A2:</span> بَذَّهُ, <abbr title=\"aorist (shows the vowel of the second consonant of the aorist/muḍāriʿ form)\">aor.</abbr> ـُ (<abbr title=\"The Tahdhīb of al-Azharī\">T</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> بَذٌّ (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) and ↓ بَذِيذَةٌ, (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) [or this may be a simple <abbr title=\"substantive, إِسْمٌ\">subst.</abbr>,] He overcame him; (<abbr title=\"The Tahdhīb of al-Azharī\">T</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>;) he surpassed him in goodliness or beauty, or in any deed: (<abbr title=\"The Tahdhīb of al-Azharī\">T</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>:) he outstripped him. (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) It is said in a <abbr title=\"tradition (hadith), حَدِيْثٌ\">trad.</abbr>, بَذَّ القَائِلِينَ He outstripped, or surpassed, and overcame, the speakers. (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) 3 باذّهُ He hastened with him; made haste, or strove, to be, or get, before him: (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>:) he vied with him in glory or excellence. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) 8 ابتذّ حَقَّهُ He took his (i. e. his own) right, or due. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) 10 استبذّ بِالأَمْرِ He was alone, with none to share, or participate, with him, in the affair; (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>;) <abbr title=\"idem quod (i.e. the same as)\">i. q.</abbr> استبدّ (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) and استقلّ. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) بَذٌّ [perhaps from the Persian بَدْ] A man slovenly with respect to his person, and poor. (<abbr title=\"Ibn al-Aʿrābī\">IAar</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tahdhīb of al-Azharī\">T</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) And بَذُّ الهَيْئَةِ, and الهَيْئَةِ ↓ بَاذُّ, A man threadbare, and shabby, or mean, in the state of his apparel; (<abbr title=\"al-Kisāʾī\">Ks</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tahdhīb of al-Azharī\">T</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Mughrib of al-Mutarrizī\">Mgh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>;) and in an evil condition with respect to it; (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>;) slovenly with respect to his person: (<abbr title=\"al-Kisāʾī\">Ks</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>:) or one who neglects the constant adornment of his person: or who adorns himself one day, and another day leaves his hair in a shaggy or dishevelled, or matted and dusty, state: (<abbr title=\"The Tahdhīb of al-Azharī\">T</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>:) or humble in his apparel, not taking pleasure therein. (<abbr title=\"Ibn al-Athīr al-Jazari\">IAth</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> بَذُّ البَخْتِ A man having evil fortune. (<abbr title=\"al-Kurāʿ, author of al-Munjid fi al-Lughah\">Kr</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b3:</span> هَيْئَةٌ بَذَّةٌ A threadbare, and shabby, or mean, state of apparel. (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b4:</span> حَالٌ بَذَّةٌ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>,) and حَالَةٌ بَذَّةٌ, (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) An evil state or condition. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b5:</span> تَمْرٌ بَذٌّ Dates that are separate, each one from another, not sticking together; like فَذٌّ: (<abbr title=\"Ibn al-Aʿrābī\">IAar</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>:) or that are scattered. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b6:</span> فَذٌّ بَذٌّ Single; sole; that is alone, or apart from others: (<abbr title=\"Ibn al-Aʿrābī\">IAar</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) and so أَحَذُّ<br><br>↓ أَبَذُّ. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) فِى هَيْئَتِهِ بَذَّةٌ, and بَذَاذَةٌ, [the latter an <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> (of بَذَّ) used as a simple <abbr title=\"substantive, إِسْمٌ\">subst.</abbr>,] In his state of apparel is slovenliness, and threadbareness, and shabbiness, or meanness. (<abbr title=\"The Tahdhīb of al-Azharī\">T</abbr>.) ↓ بَذِيذَةٌ, also, (sometimes written ↓ بَذْبَذَةٌ, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>, and so in the <abbr title=\"The Tahdhīb al-Tahdhīb (of Ibn Ḥajar al-ʿAsqalānī)\">TT</abbr> but without vowel-signs,) signifies Slovenliness with respect to one's person; or neglect of cleanliness. (<abbr title=\"The Tahdhīb of al-Azharī\">T</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) بَذِيذَةٌ, or بَذْبَذَةٌ: see بَذَّةٌ.<br><br><span class=\"sub-sense\">A2:</span> And for the former, see also بَذَّهُ.<br><br>بَاذٌّ: see بَذٌّ.<br><br><span class=\"sub-sense\">A2:</span> Also Any one overcoming, or surpassing. (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) أَبَذٌّ: see بَذٌّ."}]}}